snippet.textDisplay: Star Wars Battlefront trailers always seem to amaze me with how well executed they are, but this trailer felt more cinematic. The music, the shots, the adventure, all packed into one trailer yet feel like it’s own movie. The emotional appeal is packed everywhere, as appearances made by the most beloved characters in the saga extract our admiration for Star Wars. The ending had me in tears as seeing all 42 years of stories coming to an end with the concluding title “celebrate the saga.” Finally with the last movie, everything pieces together to create the most beautiful masterpiece of stories, characters, and memories. The Rise of Skywalker, no matter people’s opinions on it, has more significance than being just another Star Wars movie; it marks the end of an era. This movie will hold a legendary spot in the timeline of Star Wars and will hopefully be memorable for more than just being the last movie in the sequel, but instead marking the end of 42 years of history. Star Wars shouldn’t be remembered as the lousy movie franchise that made poor decisions in the past, but by the most powerful and beautiful story of triumph over evil of all time.
